{"/service/ndnp/mimtptc/batch_mimtptc_inkster_ver01/data/sn88063294/00340589130/1945111801/0124.xml":{"full_text":"Real Estate Classified\nNov. 18. 1945-\n\u2014Part 4,\nCountry Home\nBacked by FH A\nFoley Announces\nNewest Feature\nThe Federal Housing Ad\nminislration has added a now\nfeature to its program\ncountry home*.\nExpanding its facilities still\nfurther. Commissioner Ray\nmond M. Foley has notified\nmore than 13,000 banks, sav\nings and loan associations,\nand other approved lending\ninstitution* that the FHA\nstands ready to insure ft nano\ning of low pi iced homes\nlocated on small plots of land\nadiaccnt to the suburban\nareas surrounding cities.\nAIMS OF FHA\nIn his letter to the lend\ning institutions Foley said the\nFHA proposes, insofar as is\npracticable and in keeping\nwith the mandates of the Na\ntional Housing Art. to broaden\nits operations in order to ad\njust private enterprise to\nmeet more nearly the total\nhousing of this eountry.\nAccordingly, he said\nM \u00abr are sending Instruc\ntion* to our field office* to\ninclude a* eligible for mort\ngage Insurance that cla** of\nproperties which, for want\nof a heifer term, we are\ndesignating a* eountry\nhome*.\n\"Me ha\\e In mind those\nhome* in outlying area*,\nwith a small plot of land,\non which the owner resides\nnut upon the product* of\nw hich he doe* not depend\n%ur a ItvchhiMtd.\nM.K.IIM.K PROPERTY\n\u201cS ur h a projierty I*\neligible for mortgage insur\nance if it meet* our mini\nmum property requirement*\nand ha* market acceptance.\n\"It should he pari of an\nestablished neighborhood of\naimilar properties or part\nof a neighborhood to he\nestablished with proper\nsafeguard*.\n\"It is not our purpose to\nadd Impetus to the decen\ntralisation of urban area*,\nhut rather to recognize a\nMT\\ definite need and de\naire on the part of a seg\nment of the market to ||\\e\nm the t-tmlrv\n\"This ha* been going on\nfor \\ear* and the result*\nran he observed In the nut\n|\\tng areas of any