reau, Detroit Police De\npartment, and John ,1. Con-\nMfline, general superintendent\nDetroit Department of Parks\nand Recreation.\nCudillo Joins\nGarling Firm\nFred C Carling, general\nreal estate. Dearborn an\nnounred Saturday that Mark\nCudillo has\nbecome\nciated with\nI his organ i/a\n--f l tion it-, office\n\u2019Vyl manager and\nl* 1 1 g H g f\nM broker\n''l\u2018l.' 'n\nv\n-aH i\nwith the Fort\nwe (iimi o ay nt Mort\ngage Co and its affiliate*.\nH.> duration'll background\nwas with Western High\nSchool. University of Detroi*\nand the IVlrott Institute nt\n'I echnology.\nlie is a rnerrrher of Ihe So\nciety of Residential Apprais\ner* and a former member of\nthe Cnit<\u2018d Northwest Realty\nA-s-six'iatii.r..\nAttic Insulation\nA qniek_and wav tru\ncut fuel Full* ard redure win\nter heat Josses is t<> aj>p!y in\nsula* inc board on the top of\nattic floor joists or under the\nroof rafters, it is suggested.\nHousing Study\nUrged by Hart\nRef<ve teaching a derision\non pending public housing\nlegislation. Congress should\nmake provision fora thorough\nstudy to determine the prob\nable number of families which\nwill n\u00bbsjd public assistance in\nhousing in an active peace\ntime economy, L. C. Hart,\npresident ot the Producers'\nCouncil, slated Saturday.\n\u201cPlans for extending\nhousing aid oblnit aI y\nshould not he based either\non conditions which pre\nvailed during the postwar\ndepression years or on the\ntemporary need which may\nexist during the remainder\nof the reconversion period,\"\nHart said.\nFUTURE PERIOD\n\u2018To the contrary, any\npiihtie housing legislation\nadopted at this time should\nbe intended to meet the\nneed existing in the period\nstarting IX months or two\nyear* from now.\n\"Inasmuch as an n on\nnmy of virtually full em\nployment i* anticipated at\nthat time, it seems logical\nto assume that there may\nhe relatlxely few families\nun\u00ab bI e to meet their\nhousing needs without pub\nlic assistance during that\nperiod.\nPROPOSES >TI DV\n\"If a case study confirms\nthis assumption, there will\nhe no need to set up a large\nand costly program of pub\nlic housing assistance so\nlong as that condition con\ntinues.\n\"Moreover, a competent\nstudv of the public housing\nrequirements of low Income\nfamilies may show tlsit the\nmajor part of the need will\nhe centered in relatively\nfew communities where it\ncan best he met with\nlocal fund* administered by\nqikilified local citizens.\"\nBrokers\nV/fl yne Po-ici Ch\u2019eT\nTalk Set for Nov. 21\nPrescott G Brown, chair\nman of the Wayne County\nRoad Commission will ad\ndress members of the broker*\ndivision of the Detroit Rea\nEstate Board n Old** Wave\nClub Wednesday not in R\nBliss Wolfe, division chair\nman. said Saturday.\n--The speaker who w-r-H+r-'-\ncu*s the activities of tfv\ncommission, vs ill he preserve'\nhv Howard J. Ely. progran\nchairman.\nSpace Saver\nA lavatory placed on thz\nmiter wall of a shower *ta!\nsaves space as well a* co<t ir\nthe original installation, sinrt\nthe w at_cr pipes can- scrxi\nbo*h the shower and lava\ntorv. suggest* Practica\nBuilder. Chicago.\nf SEE NEW HOUSES\nNOW BEING BUILT\nBIG WIDE LOTS FOR SUE\n70 END 100 FT. WIDE\nDrive Out Schoolcraft to Beech Road\nBuy Your Land Now. Be Ready\nB. E. TAYLOR J\nEvergreen 5230 from 1 P. M. jMxy\nUntil Dark Every Day\n-YOU DON\u2019T HAVE TO WAIT\u2014\nAvailable for Immediate Delivery or Application\nFLINTKOTE\nINSULATED BRICK SIDING\niu ii irrtrrr <*r wimt\n*12.50 rn *25.00\nMatertAl Only SQ. FT. Applied Complete\n210-lb. Cedartex Thick Butt Roofing\n*5.65 e *12.00\nMaterial Only SQ. TT. Applied t ampleta\nmu\nWALL PLANKING CEILING TILE\nFOR ATTIC AM\u00bb NtACMK.M WOO MW\n*7.20 IS *35.00\nMaterial Only SQ. FT. Applied nmplet#\nU. 6. SPUNGLASS iaiciii ATlflll\nCELOTEX BATT I INSULATION\nBuy the ij A Q Q 0 f av T #m\nMaterials Hil U<3 O O Applied\nVISIT OUR WAREHOUSE AND SHOWROOMS\nOPEN\nSUNDAYS\n10 to 3\n-S' 4*4*- X-.\n\u25a0tci oiti:.. This is the 45-year-old house at 